A task requiring determining the final positions of a set of objects given their initial positions and a description of a sequence of swaps.

Q: Alice, Bob, and Claire are playing a game. At the start of the game, they are each holding a ball: Alice has a yellow ball, Bob has a blue ball, and Claire has a pink ball.
As the game progresses, pairs of players trade balls. First, Claire and Alice swap balls. Then, Alice and Bob swap balls. Finally, Claire and Bob swap balls. At the end of the game, Bob has the
Options:
(A) yellow ball
(B) blue ball
(C) pink ball
A: (A)

Q: In a game of musical chairs, five people - Alice, Bob, Claire, Dave, and Eve - are sitting around a table with five chairs. The game starts with each person sitting in a chair: Alice is in the first chair, Bob is in the second chair, Claire is in the third chair, Dave is in the fourth chair, and Eve is in the fifth chair.
As the game begins, the people start to get up and move around. First, Alice and Bob get up and move to the other side of the table, so that Alice is now in the second chair and Bob is in the first chair. Then, Claire and Dave get up and move to the other side of the table, so that Claire is now in the fourth chair and Dave is in the third chair. Finally, Eve and Claire get up and move to the other side of the table, so that Eve is now in the third chair and Claire is in the fifth chair. In the end, the person sitting in the first chair is
Options:
(A) Alice
(B) Bob
(C) Claire
(D) Dave
(E) Eve
A: (B)||
